The paper deals with cybersecurity in advanced metering infrastructure (AMI) networks, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves the use of deep recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and hyper-parameter tuning, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also utilizes time series data to detect electricity theft, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
